---

**About `.env` and secrets** — here's the mental model:
```
.env.example   ← SAFE to commit ✅  (has fake placeholder values)
.env           ← NEVER commit ❌    (has your real secret values)
```

So your `.env.example` looks like:
```
JWT_SECRET=change-this-to-something-long-and-random
PORT=3001
```

And your actual `.env` (which you create yourself, never share) looks like:
```
JWT_SECRET=k9$mN2#pL8vQ...  ← a real secret you made up
PORT=3001